docs.lead_paragraph: As couples go to court over embryos, groups argue that such cases should be decided by the legal standard used in child-custody disputes.

headline.main: Anti-Abortion Groups Join Battles Over Frozen Embryos
headline.print_headline: Groups Opposed to Abortion Join Fights on Frozen Embryos

docs.abstract: Anti-abortion groups are seeking role in court battles over frozen embryos, arguing cases should be decided according to best interests of embryos, same legal standard used in child-custody feuds;  groups' position is part of broader 'personhood' debate at center of abortion issue and raises questions over involvement of outside entities in family disputes; court battle between Jalesia McQueen and Justing Gadberry in Missouri illustrates issue's complexity.
docs.snippet: As couples go to court over embryos, groups argue that such cases should be decided by the legal standard used in child-custody disputes.
